Hmmm, after I added UUID into the error message this now passes. Is this the consequence of the strange scope tree rules?

@user1:
Ha, yeah.
In the original take, the reference to the anchor appeared only in a subquery. (And like, triply so: inside of SET OF argument, inside a select statement, inside a filter clause thereof.)
But once the error message was added, it was referred to in the scope *outside* of the SET OF argument to `assert_exists`, so that is where it gets bound...
